Half-Life 2 has been endlessly refined to get as close to perfection as could realistically be hoped. All the money - or indeed time - is on the screen. The player sees things through the eyes of Gordon Freeman, the bespectacled scientist who starred in the original 1998 Half- life. Underplaying the narrative in this way is gloriously effective.

Half-Life 2 is the best thing in its genre, and possibly, many will feel, of any genre. Running around on foot is great enough, but jumping into vehicles proves even more fun. Human foes are rendered just as well as alien ones. The stealth sections are as exhilarating as the open gun battles.

Half-Life 2 is out now for the PC. It is surely the best thing in its genre, and possibly, many will feel, of any genre. The bar has been raised so far out of sight that you have to sympathise with any game that tries to do anything remotely similar in the near future.
